40|$|Border <b>tax</b> <b>adjustments</b> for {{environmental}} <b>taxes</b> should leave imports of final goods unchanged. If intermediate and final goods markets are imperfectly competitive though, non-neutrality can result. Under Cournot behavior, an import tax {{equal to the}} environmental tax is too high, and under Bertrand, an import subsidy is the appropriate policy. Environmental Economics and Policy, International Relations/Trade,...|$|R
