30|$|When BAMs {{are based}} on Australia’s (importing country) emissions, a small impact implies that {{barriers}} imposed are small. If all sectors had the same carbon intensity, then we could expect a neutral relative price effect. Contrary to this, our results do indicate that BAMs are not neutral due to sector-specific <b>tax</b> <b>adjustments</b> leading to relative price shifts, even though the impact is rather small.|$|R
